article.description: RJ Noel passed for one touchdown and ran for two more as Sacred Heart scored four times after halftime to defeat Stony Brook 38-10 on Saturday night and maintain a perfect record.
article.headline: Sacred Heart beats Stony Brook 38-10, gets 3 scores on TOs
article.linkText: Sacred Heart beats Stony Brook 38-10, gets 3 scores on TOs
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- RJ Noel passed for one touchdown and ran for two more as Sacred Heart scored four times after halftime to defeat Stony Brook 38-10 on Saturday night and maintain a perfect record. Noel broke a halftime tie with a TD from the 1 midway through the third quarter then guided the Pioneers (4-0) on a 95-yard scoring drive capped with a 1-yard TD from Jay Croom. The backbreaker came in the fourth quarter when Sacred Heart scored 14 points in 13 seconds -- a 14-yard pass from Noel to Moses Webb with 12:59 remaining, followed by an interception returned 44 yards for a TD by Kevin Barry and 12:46 on the clock. Sacred Heart scored 17 points off turnovers against Stony Brook (2-2), which entered ranked 20th in the FCS poll. The Seawolves' Joe Carbone passed for 97 yards and Stacey Bedell gained 62 on 14 carries.
